    <h1 style="font-size: 30px;">Section 1 : Introduction to HTML</h1>
    <p>HTML (Hypertext Markup Language) is the standar markup language for creatung web pages, It provides the
        <br>structure and content of a web page.</p>

    <p>In this section, we'll explore the basic of HTML and its key elements.</p>

    <h1 style="font-size: 30;">Section 2 : HTML Paragraphs</h1>
    <p>Paragraphs are used to strcuture text content on a web page. They provide a clear separation between different
        <br>pieces of information.</p>

    <p>You can easily create paragraphs by enclosing your text within <sub>p</sub> tags </p>

    <h1 style="color: blue;">Section 3 : Styling and Formatting</h1>

    <p style="color: green;">CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) allows you to style your HTML documents, Let;s apply some styles to our
    <br>headings and paragraphs</p>

    <b style="color: red;">This text is bold,</b> <i style="color: red;">This text is italic,</i> <u style="color: red;">This text is underlined</u>

    <ol>
        <li>Ordered List Item 1</li>
        <li>Ordered List item 2</li>
        <li>Ordered List Item 3</li>
    </ol>

    <ul>
        <li>Unordered List Item 1</li>
        <li>Unordered List Item 2</li>
        <li>Unordered List Item 3</li>
    </ul>

        <p>This is blockquote, It's often used to highlights quotes or important information.</p>

